# git-push-verify — from Cursor

Canonical definition: `.claude/commands/git-push-verify.md`

**To run from Claude Code terminal:** type `/git-push-verify`

**To run manually from Cursor's terminal panel:**

### Stage
```bash
git add -A
```

### Commit (paste this whole block)
```bash
git commit -m "feat: project harness v1.0 — enforcement system, docs, and video explainer

Harness infrastructure:
- AGENTS.md charter, CLAUDE.md mandatory reads, .ai/protocols/ (2 protocols)
- .cursor/rules/: 3 auto-loaded pointer rule files
- .claude/hooks/: 4 enforcement scripts (session block, write gate, docs gate)

Documentation: docs-surface-classifier, documentation-update-flow,
.ai/docs/ baseline package, docs/ product package

Product: harness-video/ (Remotion 8-scene explainer, ~120s, 1280x720)"
```

### Push (PAT required at runtime — never stored)
```bash
# Read repo URL from config
REPO_URL=$(python3 -c "import json; d=json.load(open('.ai/config/project.json')); print(d['github']['repo_url'])")
USERNAME=$(python3 -c "import json; d=json.load(open('.ai/config/project.json')); print(d['github']['username'])")
# Type your PAT when prompted:
read -s -p "GitHub PAT: " PAT
REPO_PATH="${REPO_URL#https://github.com/}"
git push "https://${USERNAME}:${PAT}@github.com/${REPO_PATH}.git" --set-upstream origin master
unset PAT
```

### Fetch and verify
```bash
git fetch origin
git log origin/master --oneline --graph -8
git remote -v
gh repo view 2>/dev/null || echo "Visit $(git remote get-url origin)"
```

Security: PAT is read into a shell variable, used once, then immediately unset. Never written to disk.
